/*!
\page opentrep-indexer
      Command-line utility to Xapian-index a travel-related database text file

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS

<b>opentrep-indexer</b> <tt>[--prefix] [-v|--version] [-h|--help] [-b|--builtin] [-i|--input <path-to-input>] [-l|--log <path-to-output-log-file>]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e opentrep-indexer is a small program to Xapian-index the key-words
   appearing in the given input file.

\e opentrep-indexer accepts the following options:

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the Opentrep installation prefix.

 \b -v, \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of Opentrep on the standard output.

 \b -h, \b --help<br>
    Produce that message and show usage.

 \b -b, \b --builtin<br>
    The sample BOM tree can be either built-in or parsed from an input
    file.  When that option is selected, an input file must then be
    given with the -y/--yield option. When that option is not selected,
    the \b opentrep program builds a simple use case directly from internal
    hard-coded parameters (yield rules).

 \b -y, \b --yield <path-to-input-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the (CSV) input file specifying
    the yield rules.<br>

 \b -l, \b --log <path-to-output-log-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the output log file.

See the output of the <tt>`opentrep --help'</tt> command for default options.


\section sec_see_also SEE ALSO
